8.1.4 Kotlin makes number conversions explicit

	- In Kotlin, you need to apply the conversion explicitly.
		ex)
			====================================================================================
			val i = 1
			val l: Long = i.toLong() // convert explicitly
			====================================================================================

	* Kotlin requires you to convert the types explicitly so that only values of the same type are compared!


	* When conversion fails, you can use "orNull" (rather than throwing NumberFormatException)
		ex)
			====================================================================================
			fun main(){
				println("seven".toIntOrNull()) // null
			}
			====================================================================================
		